    <br>
    Over the decade since 2010, the net loss in forests globally was 4.7
    million hectares per year.However, deforestation rates were much
    significantly higher.
    The UN FAO estimate that 10 million hectares of forest were cut down
    each year.
    The world has lost one-third of its forests, but an end of deforestation is
    possible.
  </div>
  <h3>SOLUTION:</h3>
  <div class="solution">
    <img
      src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/957024/forest-trees-perspective-bright-957024.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&dpr=2&h=650&w=940"
